http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Mon 11 Apr 2016
Source: OIE, WAHID weekly disease information 2016; 29(15) [edited]
http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=20022


African horse sickness, South Africa
------------------------------------
Information received on 11 Apr 2016 from Dr Bothle Michael Modisane, Chief Director, Department of Agriculture, Forestry and Fisheries, Animal Production and Health, Pretoria, South Africa.

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 2 Apr 2016
Date of confirmation of the event: 7 Apr 2016
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: May 2015
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: African horse sickness virus
Serotype: pending
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks:
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1 (AHS_WCP_2016_001): AHS_WCP_2016_001, Drakenstein, Western Cape Province
Date of start of the outbreak: 2 Apr 2016
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm

Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Equidae / 10 / 1 / 1 / 0 / 0
Affected population: 18-month-old colt showed signs of African horse sickness and died.

Outbreak statistics: [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]
Species / morbidity rate / mortality rate / case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Equidae / 10 / 10 / 100 / 10
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive
Control measures
Measures applied: movement control inside the country; screening; quarantine; no vaccination; no treatment of affected animals.
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Equine Research Centre (private laboratory) / Equidae / real-time PCR / 7 Apr 2016 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[During 2014, 38 outbreaks of African horse sickness (AHS) were reported. All outbreaks were resolved on 16 Jun 2014, and South Africa sent a final report to the OIE on 20 Jun 2014. The serotype was identified as type 1. See updated report and map at http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/temp/reports/en_fup_0000015455_20140620_155709.pdf.

In 2015, 126 outbreaks were reported between January and June. Of 1378 susceptible animals, there were 184 reported cases, 65 reported deaths, one destroyed, and 1969 vaccinated. For more details about the locations of these outbreaks, see South Africa's OIE semi-annual report for January-June 2015 at http://tinyurl.com/zb4qkqk, and go to section 3.

Maps of South Africa can be seen at http://www.ephotopix.com/south_africa_province_map.html and http://healthmap.org/r/awB6. - Mod.CRD

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4152368,4335.]
